5|$|In {{a dispute}} {{over the use of}} the forces {{defending}} the Harpers Ferry garrison, Hooker offered his resignation, and Abraham Lincoln and General-in-Chief Henry W. Halleck, who were looking <b>for</b> <b>an</b> <b>excuse</b> to get rid of him, immediately accepted. They replaced Hooker early on the morning of June 28 with Maj. Gen. George Gordon Meade, then commander of the V Corps.|$|E
