500|$|As each {{episode of}} Inside No. 9 {{features}} new characters, the writers {{were able to}} attract actors {{who might have been}} unwilling to commit to an entire series. [...] "The Bill" [...] starred Shearsmith as Archie, Pemberton as Malcolm, Jason Watkins as Kevin, Philip Glenister as Craig, Ellie White as Anya and Callum Coates as Tim. Watkins had previously starred in Shearsmith and Pemberton's Psychoville; though the pair generally have a rule against reusing actors from Psychoville in Inside No. 9, so as [...] "to keep surprising and avoid familiarity", they broke their rule [...] "because [...] brilliant". Pemberton explained that he and Shearsmith work hard to make roles attractive to accomplished actors, claiming that Glenister had hoped he would not like the script, looking <b>for</b> <b>an</b> <b>excuse</b> to turn down a week's work in his busy schedule.|$|E
